  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/1b3d02a301f85bb8d5ef04c1ea14f45b20cf1fb9/packages/provider/wrapper.js#L29\r\n\r\nThis only works because ganache itself doesn't use its own `send` function when someone uses the alias method `sendAsync`.\r\n\r\nIf `sendAsync` is _also_ monkey patched a bunch of truffle tests fail, as if they are relying on `sendAsync`, which is an alias of `send`, not being monkey patched.\r\n\r\nOne complication is that the monkey-patch replaces the callback's `err` object with its own `Error`, and some tests rely on the original `err` object's extra properties (`err.hashes[0]`, for example).",
